_source.title: DNS Report -  At Risk Clients
_source.description: Top 100 clients (srcIP).  Each bar is srcIP address identified by Safe Network making a request to a malicious domain.  The y-axis as the macro level shows the number of requests from each source IP address.  Each color band in the bar represents a different malware family.

_source.title: DNS Report - Top 10 Malware Count
_source.description: Count of the top 10 malware families.

_source.title: DNS Report - Foreign DNS Map
_source.description: Look at where DNS requests that are not processed by the service provider DNS requests are being processed.  This report benefits from filtering out the service providers DNS infrastructure from the report.  To do this, add the SP DNS IP address to the existing ‘SP DNS’ filter.  You can then include/exclude these servers from this report.

_source.title: DNS Report - Malware by Resolver
_source.description: Shows Malware family the different DNS resolvers serving that malware.  The x-axis lists the different malware families identified by the system.  The y-axis shows the count of DNS events.  Each color band represents the number of requests to a particular DNS server.    NOTE:  To remove the SP DNS servers from the report, add the DNS server address to the “SP DNS” filter included in the report.

_source.title: DNS Report - Malware Resolvers
_source.description: Shows the different sites resolving malicious domain requests.  The x-axis lists the destination IP addresses that are resolving malicious domains.  The y-axis is the count of the number of events.  Each colored strip represents a Malware Family for that site.

_source.title: DNS Report - Malware & Associated File Types
_source.description: How malware is distributed.  Achieved by looking at each File Type associated with each malware family. Gives insight into the subscriber platform that may be impacted by the malware.

_source.title: DNS Report - Top 50 Malware Families
_source.description: Count of the top 50 malware families.  Filters allow you to remove 'Adware' families or focus on' Android'  families.

_source.title: DNS Report - Malware Over Time
_source.description: Displays the malware received each hour as a bar graph with each color representing the count of the malware family received within that hour
